OL,3,CNeonatal nurse accused of faking CV to
OL,4,Cget a senior job found guilty
OL,6,FBut when asked about the claims in
OL,7,Fcourt she was unable to answer basic
OL,8,Fquestions about how she'd entered the
OL,9,Fwar-torn country.
OL,11,FAddressing the jury, prosecutor Emma
OL,12,FHarris said Ms Nasir's actions had
OL,13,F"placed at risk the trust which the
OL,14,Fpublic can have in those employed in
OL,15,Fthe nursing profession."
OL,17,FMs Harris added that Nasir had "placed
OL,18,Fthe most vulnerable of patients at
OL,19,Frisk."
