OL,6,F"Nasir not only lied in respect of her
OL,7,Fown qualifications but also lied on
OL,8,Fbehalf of others. In doing so she
OL,9,Fbetrayed the trust of employers and
OL,10,Fcolleagues, and showed a total
OL,11,Fdisregard for the welfare and safety
OL,12,Fof vulnerable patients, putting their
OL,13,Flives at significant risk.
OL,15,FThe jury unanimously found Nasir
OL,16,Fguilty of nine charges including
OL,17,Ffraud, possession of an article for
OL,18,Fuse in fraud, use of a false
OL,19,Finstrument with intent, and securing
OL,20,Funauthorised access to computer
OL,21,Fmaterial with intent.
